The passage is in `cynewulf-elene-d2d132`, chapter 1, paragraph `p-f5d1f1`. Judas holds each of the three unearthed crosses over a dead youth on a bier — the first two produce nothing, but when the third (the True Cross, "the prince's Rood") is raised over the corpse, the youth rises immediately "with spirit endowed, together both body and soul," thereby identifying the authentic cross through resurrection.
